        <h1 class="text-33px-navy">About us</h1>
        <p class="text-18px-gray">Welcome to Sapang MIS, your portal to streamlined information and connectivity in Sapang Binangonan, Rizal. We're here to enhance communication, provide updates, and facilitate collaboration among residents, businesses, and local entities. Together, we're building a stronger, more informed community.</p>
        <h2 class="text-20px-navy">Barangay Sapang, Binangonan, Rizal</h2>
        <p class="text-18px-gray">Barangay Sapang is a vibrant and diverse community nestled within the picturesque municipality of Binangonan, located in the province of Rizal, Philippines. With a population of 2,249 residents, as recorded by the 2020 Census, Sapang contributes to the rich cultural tapestry of Binangonan and stands as a testament to the area's growth and development.</p>
        <p class="text-18px-gray">Despite its relatively small population, Barangay Sapang plays an essential role in the larger context of Binangonan. Its 0.72% representation in the municipality's total population highlights its significance as a microcosm of Binangonan's diversity and culture. Residents of Sapang contribute to the economic, social, and cultural vibrancy of Binangonan through various pursuits, from agriculture and entrepreneurship to artistic endeavors and community initiatives.</p>
        <a href="https://www.philatlas.com/luzon/r04a/rizal/binangonan/sapang.html" class="text-18px-blue-underline">View more about Barangay Sapang on PhilAtlas >></a>
        <h2 class="text-20px-navy">Barangay Mission</h2>
        <p  class="text-18px-gray">Sapang deals with pertinent changes and links activities that will create competitiveness and sustained with human and environmental development</p>
        <h2 class="text-20px-navy">Barangay Vision</h2>
        <p  class="text-18px-gray">To provide an effective and efficient services that will improve the quality of life with respect and honesty to its governance</p>
        <h2 class="text-20px-navy">Barangay Goal</h2>
        <p class="text-18px-gray">Provide effective leadership. Improve/Enhance living condition through giving seminar or livelihood. Provide continuing support to Education. Strengthen and enhance communication and partnership to other LGU. Sustainable food production in each backyard</p>
